Paper: hep-th/9604121

Date: 1996-04-19

Title: Off-shell Supersymmetry versus Hermiticity in the Superstring

Comments: 4 pages harvmac

Journal-ref: Phys.Rev.Lett. 77 (1996) 2891-2892

We point out that off-shell four-dimensional supersymmetry implies strangehermiticity properties for the N=1 RNS superstring. However, these hermiticityproperties become natural when the N=1 superstring is embedded into an N=2superstring.